Package: libghc-hlint-doc
Source: hlint
Version: 2.1.6-1
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Debian Haskell Group <pkg-haskell-maintainers@lists.alioth.debian.org>
Installed-Size: 1986
Depends: haddock-interface-31
Recommends: ghc-doc, libghc-cpphs-doc, libghc-refact-doc, libghc-src-exts-doc, libjs-mathjax
Section: doc
Priority: optional
Homepage: http://community.haskell.org/~ndm/hlint/
Description: Haskell source code suggestions; documentation
 HLint gives suggestions on how to improve your source code. It can either
 print them directly, or generate a colored HTML output.
 .
 This is the HLint library, used by programs that want to incorporate HLint's
 functionality.
 .
 This package provides the documentation for a library for the Haskell
 programming language.
 See http://www.haskell.org/ for more information on Haskell.
